title: Joe 90 Top Secret (001 - 020,027,030,031,033 + Annual & Extr
description:
Joe 90 Top Secret (001 - 020,027,030,031,033 + Annual & Extras) (1969 - 1970) (TUBCBG)


Launched in 1969, as the titles produced by the partnership between Century 21 and City Magazines were beginning to struggle, Joe 90 Secret Agent featured the adventures of Gerry Anderson's latest puppet star, the eponymous teenage secret agent Joe 90, with other strips adapting the ITC superhuman spy show The Champions, and American Sci-Fi series Land of the Giants and Star Trek, both original material rather than reprinting US comic adaptations. Joe 90 lasted thirty-four issues before being cancelled and merged into TV21 to form TV21 and Joe 90
